verse.lines:
{lang-eng}I have a song that Jesus gave me,
It was sent from heav’n above;
There never was a sweeter melody,
‘Tis a melody of love.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}In my heart there rings a melody,
There rings a melody with heaven’s harmony;
In my heart there rings a melody, there
Rings a melody of love.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}I love the Christ who died on Calv’ry,
For He washed my sins away;
He put within my heart a melody,
And I know it’s there to stay.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}‘Twill be my endless theme in glory,
With the angels I will sing;
“Twill be a song with glorious harmony,
When the courts of heaven ring.{/lang-eng}
